This paper discusses the feasibility of attributing authorship to malware binaries, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for this task, which could fall under sub-categories such as software engineering (cs.SE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the analysis of features involved in authorship attribution, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
